  quote-slide slide [¿Cómo se LLama?]
  [Exercise in rephrasing text. The following paragraph
   needs to be rephrased so that it retains its precise meaning, but
   with minor variations in the specific choice of words, punctuation,
   and so on. No new facts should be introduced or removed, but it is
   good to use synonyms and change the word order and phrasing.

   Original paragraph:];

  (* XXX update this text to match demo *)
  monospace-slide (slide
                   with MONOSPACE-FONT-SIZE = 50.0)
  [Original paragraph]
  [I then sample text a word at a time to
continue this prompt. If a line ends exactly on
the number of characters that I want (and the
next character is a space or other character that
is appropriate to end a line) then I accept the
stream so far and continue. If I exceed the line
length, I back up to the state at the beginning
of the line and try again with new random
samples. I just keep doing that until the
paragraph is complete, and we have beautifully
justified monospace text that resembles the
original. Here is an example of this paragraph
rendered in monospace:];

  (* XXX better video! *)
